# Portfolio Website Implementation Plan

The objective is to build a premium, highly aesthetic personal portfolio website to showcase your educational journey, work experience, notable projects, and certifications.

## Proposed Technologies

- **Structure**: Semantic HTML5.
- **Styling**: Vanilla CSS. We will implement a modern, state-of-the-art dark mode design with vibrant gradient accents, glassmorphism effects, modern typography (e.g., Inter or Roboto), and smooth micro-animations.
- **Logic & Interactivity**: Vanilla JavaScript for dynamic features like scroll reveal animations and smooth navigation.

## Proposed Changes

We will build a responsive, single-page website structured cleanly:

### Website Structure

#### [NEW] `index.html`
- **Hero Section**: An engaging introduction with a dynamic, animated greeting and a call-to-action to view your work.
- **Experience Timeline**: A vertical timeline visualizing your career progression and role details.
- **Education Timeline**: A similar vertical timeline detailing your university degree(s) and relevant academic highlights.
- **Projects Showcase**: A grid of interactive cards displaying your major projects, with hover effects revealing project details and technologies used.
- **Certifications**: A dedicated section highlighting your cleared certifications using sleek badge-style cards.
- **Footer**: Links to your GitHub, LinkedIn, and contact information.

#### [NEW] `styles.css`
- A comprehensive stylesheet utilizing modern CSS variables for a cohesive color palette.
- Premium styling: complex gradients, drop-shadows, and responsive flexbox/grid layouts.
- Dynamic micro-animations on hover and state changes to make the interface feel alive.

#### [NEW] `script.js`
- Logic to handle smooth scrolling between sections.
- Intersection Observer implementation to trigger fade-in and slide-up animations as the user scrolls down the page, adding a layer of polish.

## Open Questions

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Your Content**
> Do you have a resume, CV, or a link to your LinkedIn profile that you can share with me? I would love to populate the website with your actual data. If not, I can build the site with high-quality placeholder text that you can easily swap out later.

> [!TIP]
> **Design Preferences**
> Do you have any specific color preferences? (e.g., A dark theme with purple/blue neon accents, or perhaps emerald green?)

## Verification Plan

### Manual Verification
- View `index.html` in the browser to ensure all sections render correctly and the design feels premium and cohesive.
- Test scroll animations and interactive hover effects.
- Verify that the layout is fully responsive across desktop, tablet, and mobile viewport sizes.
